subSubSection.paragraph:
Elytron punctation dense, not linear, not as large as pronotum, nor widely and evenly spaced; apices not deflexed; epipleuron and suture extending beyond mid-point, not extending as a ridge around apex; epipleuron and suture not expanded in apical half; 2–4 interstitial lines, inner two do not exceed suture; elytral carina absent; viewed from beneath with specimen horizontal epipleuron at elytral base wide, covering humerus, viewed from above epipleuron arises anterior to posterior margin of MS; epipleuron a lateral ridge along most of its length; sutural margins approximate along most of length in closed elytra; lateral margins parallel-sided (slightly convex-sided in 

carolinae

).

Terrestrial; tergal plates sclerotised to margins, lateral tergal margins explanate, thickened, and covering laterotergites which are not visible from above; arrangement of plates in ventral aspect of thorax and abdomen agrees with that described (
Ballantyne & Lambkin, 2000
; 
Ballantyne & Menayah, 2002
). Protergum W> L, tubercles absent along anterior margin, posterolateral corners round, and median line with non-ridged margins; median line extends to anterior and posterior margins of most terga; punctures in anterior half of terga 2–10 larger than rest; posterolateral corners of terga 1–8 rounded entire, of tergum 12 produced narrowly; median posterior margins of terga 1–11 lacking either rounded or pointed projections; lacking brush of hairs around tarsal claws; mandibles lacking inner teeth; antennal segment 3 short, sense cone adjacent to segment 3 short and wide; with laterosternites on abdominal segments 1–8.
